Some-more_key2: To find the length of an object we can use builtin functions Object.`keys`() either we can use  Object.values().
Some-more_key5: Object.`keys`(objectName) will give you the list of property names.
Some-more_key6: So, Object.`keys`(birds) will give me the list i.e.,
Some-more_key7:
[ 'name', 'type', 'ScientificName' ]
And when we use length on it , it gives 3. hooray!.....
Some-more_key9: Object.`keys`(objectName) will give you the list of property names.
Some-more_key10: Object.values(objectName) will give you the list of values.
Some-more_key13: Object.values(objectName) will give you the list of property values.
Some-more_key14: So, Object.`keys`(birds) will give me the list i.e.,
Some-more_key15:
[ 'Bald Eagle', 'Hawk', 'HaliaeetusLeucocephalus' ]
And when we use length on it , it gives 3. hooray!.....
